                Online Pathways
              


















Taking a Gap Year? Stay on Track. Get Ahead.
Have your plans to enroll in college this spring changed due to COVID-19? Are you taking a gap year and want to enroll in affordable university courses? Taking online courses at UIC lets you stay close to home and stay on track for graduation — while you explore your options and gain practical experience working.
UIC’s Online Pathways makes it easy to take online courses and earn college credit. You can register for general education courses in the humanities, social sciences and natural sciences or courses in a specific discipline such as business, computer science, engineering and education. The spring term begins January 9th.

Access High Quality, Affordable University Courses
Learn Anywhere – 100% Online
Study with Nationally Recognized Faculty







